{
  "doc_id": "55530",
  "text": "5. Decompensated cirrhosis Studies of lamivudine in patients with decompensated cirrhosis showed that lamivudine treatment is well tolerated and can stabilize or improve liver function in patients with decompensated cirrhosis thereby obviating or delaying the need for liver transplant. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] However, these studies showed that clinical benefit takes 3-6 months, and that HCC can occur even among patients with clinical improvement. Thus, prompt initiation of treatment and continued HCC surveillance are warranted.",
